lign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uzistrix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zistrix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(8/2/02 4:48:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1814.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dragon loot is NBG for a Reason</span><hr size=1> Vox/Naggy NBG loot pickup raids are the biggest fucking joke I ever heard.  Don't get me wrong, I am level 60 and haven't been there for a long ass time.  But the situation is still the same today:  I hear &quot;Open naggy raid loot is NBG !!!&quot;  Then I do a /who all announcer: 45 monk.  Of course its a melee saying NBG, the only good items that drop fron naggy and vox are melee items.  The only exceptions are vox with torbins and the staff of forbidden rights.  But the only item on par with a CoF or RBB is the staff of forbidden rights.  Still, leveing nothing for the int caster.  I remember the weight reduce bags were always a debate because the monks would say that they needed them.  Anyway, this is why casters avoid these type of raids as the loot has never been and never will be balanced.<br><br>Zistrix Logistics<br>Phantasmist <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/usoledorin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>soledorin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(8/2/02 5:06:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1814.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dragon loot is NBG for a Reason</span><hr size=1> Sorry NBG is just laughable these days. I would never attend any Naggy/Vox raids unless all were able to roll on loot do do with what ever they want with it after they have rolled and won.<br><br><br>Ibudin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/udarusgrey.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Darus Grey</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(8/2/02 6:03:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1814.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dragon loot is NBG for a Reason</span><hr size=1> NBG actually worked very well with me...outta hundreds of items over the years...I tend to keep track of them, and only a small handfool were ever sold, and a surprisingly large amount were given back as time went on, well I agree this wont always work, I benefited from having a raiding group at my vox raids that was very consistant(same people over and over again). <p><a href="http://www.darusgrey.com"><img border="0" src="http://www.darusgrey.com/darussig3.jpg" width="432" height="120"></a></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/bayonaero.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dreadnok>Dreadnok </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(8/2/02 10:00:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1814.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> win !</span><hr size=1> I asked a GM how you win in Everquest. He said &quot;When the game dies, whoever has the most stuff wins.&quot; I replied with a sort of gasp as I looked at all the toons running around me racing to npcs and bragging about kills. Then the most strange thing happened, the GM sent me another tell. <br><br>&quot;What a bunch of suckers, eh?&quot; He said. <br><br>Well, anyways..go win !<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uzistrix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zistrix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(8/2/02 10:23:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1814.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: win !</span><hr size=1> One word comes to mind Dread:  Hypocrite.<br><br>Zistrix Logistics<br>Phantasmist <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ukiradureatani.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kiradure Atani</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(8/2/02 10:29:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1814.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: win !</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> NBG actually worked very well with me...outta hundreds of items over the years...I tend to keep track of them, and only a small handfool were ever sold, and a surprisingly large amount were given back as time went on, well I agree this wont always work, I benefited from having a raiding group at my vox raids that was very consistant(same people over and over again). <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>I know the drill... I havent done Vox the past couple weeks but thats how shit works.  You offer up the chance of &quot;Need before Greed&quot; to ensure that people feel they're getting a fair chance.<br><br>I know a LOT of people that come to my raids that are after certain items that they cant purchase... or have that melee alt that wants the RBB or whatever.  I can think of a good number of people that have their back shelf alt that they play whenever they hear about these raids.  And I love those people to death because I know they're not gonna sell their stuff.<br><br>Not all raids are made of these people.  But that is who these raids are for.  I dont do the raids for the greedy people who take their RBB and sell it.  I do them for Tienshihan who wants the eyepatch and has been to countless raids led by me or with me alongside him.  (Tien is a cleric but you prolly dont know him).  I dont do these raids for Lachdenen who decided to sell his RBB cause he was getting his epic (I'm not passing judgement on him but sufficed to say he made a good 30-40k along with getting a nice haste item).<br><br>Shit happens, thats the way the cookie crumbles.  I offer those that want it a chance for loot when I host a raid, as does anyone else who hosts one.  I also offer the greedy bastards a chance to win an item to sell.<br><br>I would rather offer the casters a chance to win an item they will either sell or use than offer them the chance to win an item they have to sell since they cant use it.  Thats what I think.. its how I run things.  Seems to be the majority opinion anyways.<br><br>What you do with your loot is your own business.  But Lachdanen for example was told never to come to any of my hosted raids ever again (even though he would probably get 53 soon and not be available too anyways.)  Tien and anyone else who follows and abides by my rules is and always will be welcome at any raids I host.<br><br>Open raids need to have set rules.  I set my rules and state that if you have a problem with my rules, or any decisions I might make, that you should stay away.  Not all rules are ones that hold to your standards, but those who attend the raids must accept those rules.  If not, tough shit.  Maybe you think NBG lotto is shit and you'd do Santa Clause loot or whatever if you hosted one.  <br><br>You know the saying about opinions and assholes...  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uzistrix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zistrix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(8/2/02 11:14:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1814.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: win !</span><hr size=1> NBG is only good for guild situations where there is a long term dedication of equipping ALL members. <br><br>NBG is bullshit in pickup raids or groups because eventually the item WILL be sold.  Eventually your friend that won the eyepatch WILL sell it.  It's inevitable.  NBG vox/naggy raids turn into spy contests to see who sold their NBG loot first so that the players that didn't win shit can slander them and post nasty things about them on messageboards.<br><br>Wake up and realize that NBG is completely ludicrous.  The loot isn't balanced, the winners will ALL sell eventually and that is fact. <br><br>Take my real life example about a year  ago.  My enchanter at level 49 got an invite to a vox raid that was going to be NBG (the leaders of the raid were all melees).  Knowing that the RBB was the only good loot from vox I proceeded to log out my chanter and into my level 47 monk where I sent a tell and got into the raid on the condition that I knew how to skillfully pull ice giants.  <br><br>We wiped to vox the first time due to lack of enchanters and clerics.  <br><br>The 2nd time we pulled off a miracle with 1 cleric and 1 chanter.  RBB, white dragonscale, and the 100% weight reduce bag dropped along with a shitty spear.  The raid leaders said that NBG kicks in so monks and melees roll for RBB and bag.  <br><br>This started and uproar of all casters who had been at this raid for 4 hours and were just now guaranteed that they wouldn't even have a CHANCE at winning a damn thing.  Despite the mess the roll commenced.  With only 8 or 9 melees present the roll did not have too bad of odds.  Well, I won the roll and almost crapped my pants.  One of the co-leaders started getting angry.  There was a long pause while I was waiting for the trade window.  The co-leader that did not have the item said that the other leader was his friend in RL and refused to give the RBB to me because I was a late invite (he had the 2nd highest roll).  After some harsh words back and forth he finally gave it up.  He did however, win the bag.<br><br>For the next couple weeks when I would play my monk I would receive tells and inspections from people from the raid, obviously checking up on me.  They were just waiting for the opportunity to slander me.<br><br>Well, I sold that RBB later on that 2nd week and my monk has served as a mule since then, but my chanter benefited greatly from the large amount of platinum I had received.<br><br>This is the reason I posted on this thread, I have been there before and seen what NBG does to raids.  Instead of the players leaving the raid with the feeling of accomplishment and fairness of reward, they leave with animosity and regret.<br><br>Kiradure, since you seem to be one of these raid leaders, can you enlighten me about the positive aspects of NBG after reading my experience?<br><br>Zistrix Logistics<br>Phantasmist <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/bayonaero.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=mojozek>Mojozek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(8/3/02 12:15:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1814.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> lol </span><hr size=1> wardaorm, wer