hat weighs .4?  Most monks I know that come would TREASURE that bag for their life.  Not everyone is going to join IvM or EW.  Odds are likely that a melee that wins an RBB and doesnt upgrade to epic haste will be wearing that a LONG time before they can upgrade 4% of that haste with a CoF.<br><br>Times change, people grow, and I can accept that.  But all of these items will NOT be sold.  Some will be kept forever and some will be discarded once useless (Rez staff with no charges) or passed on to twinks (my patch).  Some are sought by high level players.. I know several wizzies interested in the Cloak now, and I doubt anyone with decent nuking power will EVER ditch a cloak with Improved Damage not true and even I can be a testament to that.III on it.<br><br>Believing that all items are sold is skewing the facts, its simply <br><br>---------------------------------------<br><br>I'm not going to say you disgust me or anything, but your actions make you the type of person that I stated that i do *NOT* do these raids for.  But not everyone would follow your greedy actions.  It doesnt make a difference to you and I dont really care.  I dont spy on everyone who wins, and I forget 85% of them.  Unless I see a familiar name in the bazaar channel (Lachdenen) i wont ever keep dibs on someone or inspect them every 5 ticks to make sure they still have their RBB.<br><br>-------------------------------------<br><br>The positive aspects?  Another living testament.  The people who dont walk away like you just to sell the item to benefit your greed or another character or your bank are the positive aspects.<br><br>I can think of a monk in Phoenix still enjoying an RBB (I think).  Angeal has her white scale and is a few short steps form her epic.  Anaa *has* her epic, and I dont think her guild was raiding Gorenaire nor had 50K+ to blow on a scale.  Would she have her epic if it werent for NBG?  Maybe, but it cuts her chance to about nil with 40ish people rolling on an 